1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,560
Oh, yes.

2
00:00:02,560 --> 00:00:04,060
Okay, where does it hurt?

3
00:00:04,060 --> 00:00:06,300
Just all over.

4
00:00:06,300 --> 00:00:09,800
I don't want to do anything dying.

5
00:00:09,800 --> 00:00:10,900
No, that's not how it works.

6
00:00:10,900 --> 00:00:14,000
You have to point to a specific part of the body.

7
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,900
Right there.

8
00:00:15,900 --> 00:00:17,600
Abdomen.

9
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:18,640
Mencies.

10
00:00:18,640 --> 00:00:19,640
Maybe.

11
00:00:19,640 --> 00:00:21,480
The uterus contracts after your egg passes through it.

12
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:23,020
No, I don't have eggs.

13
00:00:23,020 --> 00:00:24,580
So when did this start?

14
00:00:24,580 --> 00:00:26,180
About 10 minutes ago.

15
00:00:26,180 --> 00:00:27,680
When I came in with the paperwork?

16
00:00:27,680 --> 00:00:28,680
Mm-hmm.

17
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:31,200
About 40 times a year, Michael gets really sick

18
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:33,440
but has no symptoms.

19
00:00:33,440 --> 00:00:36,540
Dwight is always gravely concerned.

20
00:00:36,540 --> 00:00:39,880
Oh, is it possible you ate food that contained animal waste?

21
00:00:39,880 --> 00:00:41,280
It's possible.

22
00:00:41,280 --> 00:00:42,580
Michael?

23
00:00:42,580 --> 00:00:44,380
David Wallace is online.

24
00:00:44,380 --> 00:00:45,820
CFO?

25
00:00:45,820 --> 00:00:46,960
Oh.

26
00:00:46,960 --> 00:00:48,120
All right, everybody out.

27
00:00:48,120 --> 00:00:50,120
Out, out, out.

28
00:00:50,120 --> 00:00:51,120
Okay.

29
00:00:51,120 --> 00:00:53,720
To what do I owe this great honor, David Wallace?

30
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:55,260
Michael, I am calling...

31
00:00:55,260 --> 00:00:58,440
Abramit?

32
00:00:58,460 --> 00:01:00,460
Jan?

33
00:01:00,460 --> 00:01:01,560
Is Jan there?

34
00:01:01,560 --> 00:01:03,300
Jan is out of town right now.

35
00:01:03,300 --> 00:01:06,800
Oh, you sigh like Jan.

36
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:09,040
I broke Jan's heart, David, and I feel awful.

37
00:01:09,040 --> 00:01:11,180
It was...

38
00:01:11,180 --> 00:01:14,080
It was never my intention to ruin a life.

39
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:16,180
But you know what?

40
00:01:16,180 --> 00:01:17,480
Sometimes...

41
00:01:17,480 --> 00:01:18,180
Michael?

42
00:01:18,180 --> 00:01:20,480
You just gots to get your freak on.

43
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:21,020
Michael?

44
00:01:21,020 --> 00:01:21,480
Yeah.

45
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:22,080
Michael?

46
00:01:22,080 --> 00:01:23,160
Hmm.

47
00:01:23,160 --> 00:01:25,920
I am calling to see if you would come down

48
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:27,620
and interview for a job.

49
00:01:27,640 --> 00:01:30,140
We have opening up in corporate.

50
00:01:30,140 --> 00:01:30,840
Really?

51
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:32,080
A week from today.

52
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:34,440
Bring your first quarter stats and your recommendation

53
00:01:34,440 --> 00:01:36,520
for who would take over this grand branch.

54
00:01:36,520 --> 00:01:38,160
Wow.

55
00:01:38,160 --> 00:01:41,560
I wish I had prepared something to say.

56
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:42,360
That's not necessary.

57
00:01:42,360 --> 00:01:47,820
May God guide you in your quest.

58
00:01:47,820 --> 00:01:48,660
Yes.

59
00:01:57,620 --> 00:02:21,460
Okay.

60
00:02:21,460 --> 00:02:24,800
Everybody have their towels and swimsuits.

61
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:26,140
We have about an hour and a half.

62
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:28,660
I suggest that you all go potty now,

63
00:02:28,660 --> 00:02:32,000
and then we will be congregating on the partay bus.

64
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,240
Fun on wheels.

65
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:35,040
Only way to travel.

66
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:36,140
Besides a monorail.

67
00:02:36,140 --> 00:02:38,580
Well, Bob was going to just drive me.

68
00:02:38,580 --> 00:02:39,280
No.

69
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:39,780
No, no, no.

70
00:02:39,780 --> 00:02:40,940
No guests today.

71
00:02:40,940 --> 00:02:42,540
Classic gang only.

72
00:02:42,540 --> 00:02:43,740
Just us good friends.

73
00:02:43,740 --> 00:02:46,680
And Karen and Andy.

74
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:48,580
Sometimes Michael gets nostalgic,

75
00:02:48,580 --> 00:02:51,780
and he talks about the classic gang.

76
00:02:51,780 --> 00:02:56,120
That's Michael, me, Jim, Dwight, Angela, Kevin, Oscar, Stanley,

77
00:02:56,120 --> 00:03:00,500
Phyllis, Creed, Meredith, Kelly, and Ryan.

78
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:02,840
We're a regular Oceans 11.

79
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:04,620
Jim?

80
00:03:04,620 --> 00:03:06,780
David Wallace is calling for you.

81
00:03:06,780 --> 00:03:07,280
Oh.

82
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:07,780
Okay.

83
00:03:10,820 --> 00:03:13,180
Hello?

84
00:03:13,180 --> 00:03:13,680
Hey, David.

85
00:03:20,460 --> 00:03:22,580
Sure.

86
00:03:22,580 --> 00:03:24,660
Oscar, you brought your Speedo, I assume?

87
00:03:24,660 --> 00:03:25,580
I don't wear a Speedo.

88
00:03:25,580 --> 00:03:28,280
Well, you can't swim in leather pants.

89
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:32,840
I'm just yanking your chain.

90
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:34,200
Not literally.

91
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:34,880
Oh, I'm excited.

92
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:36,120
Today is beach day.

93
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:38,560
Michael is taking the whole office to the beach.

94
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:41,720
So I'm wearing my bathing suit underneath my shirt.

95
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:43,000
Oh, yeah.

96
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,560
I packed it in my purse.

97
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:46,880
Anybody need sunblock?

98
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:48,360
Got SPF 30.

99
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:50,400
Oh, you know what?

100
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:52,000
You're not going.

101
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:53,000
It's beach day.

102
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,000
Yeah, I know.

103
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,200
I'm sorry, Toby.

104
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:58,580
We, um, somebody has to stay here.

105
00:03:58,580 --> 00:04:02,780
I want today to be a beautiful memory that the staff and I

106
00:04:02,780 --> 00:04:07,660
share after I have passed on to New York.

107
00:04:07,660 --> 00:04:12,420
And if Toby is a part of it, then it'll suck.

108
00:04:12,420 --> 00:04:13,940
Hey.

109
00:04:13,940 --> 00:04:15,900
Want my sunscreen?

110
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:17,580
Oh, great.

111
00:04:17,580 --> 00:04:19,540
I forgot mine, and I'm wearing a two-piece.

112
00:04:19,540 --> 00:04:21,180
Uh-huh.

113
00:04:21,180 --> 00:04:21,700
Thanks, Toby.

114
00:04:25,580 --> 00:04:27,940
Hey, Pam.

115
00:04:27,940 --> 00:04:29,860
You broke up with your boyfriend

116
00:04:29,860 --> 00:04:31,380
and then kept working together.

117
00:04:31,380 --> 00:04:32,940
How did that work out?

118
00:04:32,940 --> 00:04:33,620
You remember?

119
00:04:33,620 --> 00:04:35,860
You fired Roy for attacking Jim,

120
00:04:35,860 --> 00:04:39,340
and I don't talk to him anymore, really.

121
00:04:39,340 --> 00:04:41,380
Acrimonious.

122
00:04:41,380 --> 00:04:43,340
I have a very important job for you today.

123
00:04:43,340 --> 00:04:45,060
I thought we were just having fun at the beach.

124
00:04:45,060 --> 00:04:45,560
We are.

125
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:46,140
We are.

126
00:04:46,140 --> 00:04:49,180
But I would like you to take notes,

127
00:04:49,180 --> 00:04:51,980
and I want you to find out about people's character.

128
00:04:51,980 --> 00:04:55,060
You know, not their hotness, per se,

129
00:04:55,060 --> 00:04:58,320
but their humor and their charisma

130
00:04:58,320 --> 00:05:01,360
and the indefinable quality that makes

131
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:03,280
you all glad to follow me.

132
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:07,120
What happens to a company if somebody takes a boss away?

133
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:09,360
I will answer your question with a question.

134
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:12,880
It's like what happens to a chicken.

135
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:17,520
When you take its head away, it dies.

136
00:05:17,520 --> 00:05:20,720
Unless you find a new head.

137
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:23,200
I need to see which one of these people

138
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:27,420
have the skills to be a chicken head.

139
00:05:27,420 --> 00:05:30,020
You want me to write down people's indefinable qualities?

140
00:05:30,020 --> 00:05:31,580
I want you to write down everything

141
00:05:31,580 --> 00:05:34,100
that people are doing all day and then type it up

142
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:36,060
in a way that is helpful.

143
00:05:36,060 --> 00:05:37,540
Right?

144
00:05:37,540 --> 00:05:39,600
I have the most boring job in the office,

145
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:45,020
so why wouldn't I have the most boring job on beach day?

146
00:05:45,020 --> 00:05:49,540
This way to the pate, Buzz.

147
00:05:49,540 --> 00:05:53,020
I just want to lie on the beach and eat hot dogs.

148
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:54,600
That's all I've ever wanted.

149
00:05:57,600 --> 00:06:00,680
Um, what the hell?

150
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:02,400
It's a bus that takes you to a party.

151
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:04,240
Here we go.

152
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:09,440
Um, I forgot my sluggle.

153
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:11,440
Here we go. Come on.

154
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:13,120
Okay, everybody here?

155
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,320
Yeah!

156
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:20,520
Then, Mr. Driver, we are off like a herd of turtles.

157
00:06:20,520 --> 00:06:22,520
Johnny Carson.

158
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:25,520
Johnny Carson.

159
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:38,000
Seat belts fasten, folks.

160
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,420
Safety first.

161
00:06:39,420 --> 00:06:40,620
Hey, what is all this?

162
00:06:40,620 --> 00:06:42,120
Nothing.

163
00:06:42,120 --> 00:06:43,280
If I guess, will you tell me?

164
00:06:43,280 --> 00:06:44,280
No.

165
00:06:44,280 --> 00:06:45,280
Please?

166
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:46,280
No.

167
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:47,280
Is that a sumo show?

168
00:06:47,280 --> 00:06:48,280
No, no.

169
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:49,280
I know.

170
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:50,280
We're putting on a play for Japanese investors.

171
00:06:50,280 --> 00:06:51,280
No, we are not.

172
00:06:51,280 --> 00:06:52,280
Please tell me.

173
00:06:52,540 --> 00:06:53,540
You are really annoying me.

174
00:06:53,540 --> 00:06:56,540
If you don't knock it off, I'm never going to tell you anything ever again.

175
00:06:56,540 --> 00:06:57,540
Stop it.

176
00:06:57,540 --> 00:06:58,540
Stop it.

177
00:06:58,540 --> 00:06:59,540
Stop it.

178
00:06:59,540 --> 00:07:01,540
Can we please pull over at the next rest stop?

179
00:07:01,540 --> 00:07:02,540
No.

180
00:07:02,540 --> 00:07:04,540
We're only ten minutes from the lake.

181
00:07:04,540 --> 00:07:05,540
Pull over.

182
00:07:05,540 --> 00:07:06,540
Pull over.
